article.description: — Sam Brown scored 16 points as Pennsylvania beat Monmouth 76-61 on Sunday.
article.headline: Brown helps Pennsylvania earn 76-61 victory over Monmouth
article.linkText: Brown helps Pennsylvania earn 76-61 victory over Monmouth
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Sam Brown scored 16 points as Pennsylvania beat Monmouth 76-61 on Sunday. Brown also added six rebounds for the Quakers (5-3). Tyler Perkins added 15 points while going 5 of 10 from the floor, including 3 for 4 from 3-point range, and 2 for 3 from the line, and they also had seven rebounds. Augustus Gerhart had 10 points and finished 5 of 7 from the floor. The Hawks (4-3) were led by Jaret Valencia, who recorded 16 points. Jack Collins added 12 points and four assists for Monmouth. Nikita Konstantynovskyi also had eight points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
